The disease has done its work: an immense weakness makes it impossible for him to take himself to the toilet or just eat himself.
Resigned, he looks at a delicious breakfast and agrees to help him eat.
He is brave and even smiles, speaks with strangers who stop with him, brings him medications, offer a bath.
The courage to normal death.
“My greatest desire is to get rid of that diarrhea, that humiliates me,” he says.
