This is a file cutting phase; i.e. the transformation of a huge file into a shorter and unique digital footprint.
Computers will "receive" this new transaction and add a number to it, only then they will "scroll" the whole.
The goal is to find a number that provides a specific footprint (equally zero at the beginning).
Once this number is found, the other nodes will easily check its correctness.
The transaction will then appear indestructiblely connected to the chain of all other transactions; any modification would result in a change of footprint.
If a user wants to pay twice the same money in order to fraud very quickly (in ten minutes), the network will only confirm one of the two transactions - the other will be abandoned because each of them has a different footprint.
