The summit took place without the presidents of Brazil (Dilma Rouseff), Venezuela (Hugo Chavez), Bolivia (Evo Morales) and Argentina (Cristina Kirchner).
Paraguay was excluded from the Unasur in 2011 after the demise of then President Fernand Luga and did not participate in the meeting.
The host president Ollanta Humala was charged with opening morning speeches and ending the summit in Lima shortly after noon.
