He that actions are supported to improve cooperation in the fight against civil uncertainty and international organized crime, to improve the availability of drugs and cheap internet in all corners of South America and to joint and effective measures against the risks of natural disasters.
When Europe is in crisis, “the economic consolidation (Latin America) must not have a winning essence, but it must serve to expand our productivity and show our peoples a better future,” Humala added.
“We have decided to prioritize a group of 31 symbolic projects that will improve the transport connections of different places in South America, especially rural and border areas... so that our countries are better connected and create new economic ties,” the Peruvian president said in a speech.
